cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.EM

The paper discusses the implementation of machine learning algorithms on hardware, which falls under the category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture for Artificial Intelligence). The paper specifically addresses issues related to device variation and insufficient interconnections, which are relevant to cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of neural networks and pruning techniques also suggests relevance to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the mention of memory technology and interconnection overhead suggests relevance to cs.EM (Embedded Systems).
